<h2>Requirements for Indian Students Pursuing MBBS Abroad</h2>

<h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
<p>The National Medical Commission (NMC) sets guidelines for Indian students pursuing MBBS abroad. To apply for MBBS abroad, Indian students must meet the eligibility standards set by the NMC, which include:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Educational Requirements:</strong> Candidates must have passed 10+2 from a recognised board with at least 50% marks in PCB subjects. The aggregate score for reserved category applicants (SC/ST/OBC) is 40 per cent.</li>
    <li><strong>Age Requirements:</strong> Candidates must be at least 17 years of age as on December 31 of the admission year.</li>
    <li><strong>NEET Requirements:</strong> Candidates must have completed the NEET UG exam and must have a valid NEET scorecard.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Entrance Exam To Study MBBS Abroad</h3>
<p>If an Indian student wishes to study MBBS abroad, he or she must first complete the National Eligibility-cum-Entrance Test (NEET) for undergraduates. The Medical Council of India (MCI) mandated NEET for Indian students. Aside from NEET, students seeking to study MBBS abroad may be required to take English proficiency exams such as IELTS and TOEFL to demonstrate their ability to speak and understand English. However, these examinations are not mandated in all countries.</p>

<h3>Admission Process For Studying MBBS Abroad</h3>
<p>The admission process for Indian students in MBBS abroad programmes is determined by their Class 12 PCB subject grades and NEET scores. Admission to foreign medical colleges is based on merit. Here are step-by-step instructions:</p>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Choose a medical university in your chosen destination.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Complete the application form with relevant information.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Before submitting your application form, attach any relevant papers.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Get the admission letter from the university.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 5:</strong> To apply for a student visa, submit your original passport and other required documents.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 6:</strong> Pay your first-year tuition expenses.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 7:</strong> Pack your bags for your MBBS abroad.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 8:</strong> Board your flight to the MBBS destination.</li>
</ol>


<h2>Documents Required For MBBS Admission Abroad</h2>
<p>Any Indian student wishing to study MBBS abroad must submit the following documents while applying for admission in foreign medical universities:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Scanned copies of 10th and 12th grade marksheets and pass certificates.</li>
    <li>Admission letter</li>
    <li>Birth certificate</li>
    <li>Medical certificate and HIV report</li>
    <li>Coloured passport-size pictures</li>
    <li>Caste Certificate (Optional)</li>
    <li>Student visa</li>
    <li>Valid passport with one-year validity</li>
    <li>NEET Scorecard</li>
    <li>Air tickets</li>
</ul>
<p>Most countries require translated copies of the above-mentioned documents into their national language for the admission process.</p>

